Attention Preschool and Kindergarten families! We apologize for the confusion with multiple surveys. The initial survey sent last week was used to collect feedback on possible face-to-face models for instruction. The most recent survey (attached here) will ask you to decide which of the options presented are best for your family for the first trimester. Kindly complete one survey for every child you have enrolled in preschool and/or kindergarten for September 2020.

Note-If you have already completed this survey, you DO NOT need to resubmit.

Congratulations to the team for a strong showing!
#proud2bMillstone

post_text:
"Dear POW/MIA Program" - A two-part program in which the students are visited by local veterans from the Vietnam war and are taught about the meaning of the POW/MIA flag and its importance. The students are encouraged to find out about their military family tree and bring in pictures and stores to share during part two, which will be Oct 30. Meanwhile, the students are each given the name of a US soldier who is currently listed as missing in action from Vietnam. In social studies class, the students will write letters of appreciation and comfort to those soldiers‚Äô family members.
#proud2bMillstone üá∫üá∏
